race.comment: Big prize money and very tough to sort out. BOSUSTOW (5) gets the verdict after an excellent return over this distance in the Bill Ritchie last start, chiming in late but just coming up short. Group One placegetter at this trip. Fitter and from a nice alley looks sure to feature. WILLYDOIT (10) sustained a minor injury and was a late scratching from the Epsom last Saturday. Caught the eye first-up over this trip in the Tramway, weaving through traffic late. Derby winner who can perform over these shorter trips. HEADLEY GRANGE (2) hit a new peak when successful in the Gr 3 Cameron at Newcastle recently. Outside gate dampens the enthusiasm but he will run well as always. AIRMAN (4) can improve third-up on a seven-day turnaround.
